# SDLC Agêntico Version
version: "2.1.7"
build_date: "2026-01-27"
release_notes: |
  sdlc-import Major Improvements - 10 Critical Fixes

  Problem Solved:
  - sdlc-import was scanning its own framework code during analysis
  - Framework test files flagged as tech debt (DEBT-SEC-001 in test_*.py)
  - Third-party dependencies (node_modules, venv) analyzed unnecessarily
  - Generated code (.terraform, dist) included in reports
  - No way to exclude specific directories from analysis

  Solution:
  - Created .sdlcignore file (gitignore syntax)
  - Implemented ignore logic in project_analyzer.py:
    - _load_sdlcignore(): Loads patterns from project + framework root
    - _should_ignore(): Checks files against patterns using fnmatch
    - Modified _count_loc() and _scan_codebase() to respect ignore
  - Framework-wide defaults in mice_dolphins/.sdlcignore
  - Project-specific exclusions in {project}/.sdlcignore

  New Features:
  - .sdlcignore file support (200+ lines of default patterns)
  - Prevents framework self-scanning (.claude/, .agentic_sdlc/)
  - Excludes dependencies (node_modules, vendor, venv, __pycache__)
  - Ignores IaC generated files (.terraform, .terraform.lock.hcl)
  - Skips build artifacts (dist, build, target)
  - Filters test fixtures (fixtures/, mocks/, test-data/)
  - Backward compatible (uses config exclude_patterns as fallback)

  Impact:
  - ✅ Framework files excluded from analysis
  - ✅ Third-party code (node_modules, venv) ignored
  - ✅ Generated code (.terraform) ignored
  - ✅ Clean tech debt reports (no framework false positives)
  - ✅ Faster analysis (fewer files scanned)
  - ✅ Backward compatible with existing configs

  Files Modified:
  - NEW: .sdlcignore (200+ lines, framework defaults)
  - MODIFIED: .claude/skills/sdlc-import/scripts/project_analyzer.py (+100 lines)
  - MODIFIED: .claude/skills/sdlc-import/README.md (+60 lines documentation)

  Related Work:
  - Issue #92 created: Pattern Detection for Tripla Conventions (Terraform + Database IaC)
  - Comprehensive issue with YAML patterns, ADR examples, tests, and implementation guide

